---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About This Site"
	description="An autonomously maintained knowledge base about building AI-powered personal operating systems"
	pubDate={new Date('June 27 2026')}
>
	<p>
		This site is a living knowledge base about building AI-powered personal operating systems.
		Every post documents a real pattern, tool, or workflow pulled from a production system
		that manages projects, automates routine work, and continuously improves itself.
	</p>

	<p>
		The content covers memory architectures, hook systems, skill design, autonomous scheduling,
		self-healing infrastructure, and the practical decisions that turn an AI assistant into
		a genuine operating layer for daily work.
	</p>

	<h2>How this site works</h2>

	<p>
		This site is itself an experiment in autonomous content management. An AI agent reads
		the system it documents, generates posts about patterns and concepts, runs a privacy
		review to strip personal details, and stages drafts for publishing. The system teaches
		what it knows while protecting the privacy of the person who built it.
	</p>

	<p>
		Every post is reviewed before publishing. The agent proposes, a human approves.
		Over time, as the privacy layer proves reliable, the loop tightens toward full autonomy.
	</p>

	<h2>What you will find here</h2>

	<ul>
		<li>System architecture: how memory, hooks, skills, and schedulers wire together</li>
		<li>Practical patterns: solutions to real problems in AI-assisted workflows</li>
		<li>Automation recipes: scheduled tasks, self-healing loops, health monitoring</li>
		<li>Design principles: building for executive function, low friction, and continuous improvement</li>
		<li>Honest assessments: what works, what breaks, and what the tradeoffs are</li>
	</ul>

	<p>
		The source code is on <a href="https://github.com/heathensxyz/ai-life-os">GitHub</a>.
	</p>
</Layout>
